## Peripheral Power Gating

### Clock Gating Checklist

- [ ] Unused peripheral clocks disabled at boot
- [ ] Peripherals clocked only when transaction is active
- [ ] GPIO pins configured to lowest-power state when unused (input with pull-down, or analog)
- [ ] ADC powered down between conversions
- [ ] Radio / modem powered down between transmissions
- [ ] Display backlight dimmed or off when inactive

### Peripheral State Machine

```
       +-------+    enable     +--------+    transact    +--------+
       |  OFF  | -----------> | IDLE   | ------------> | ACTIVE |
       +-------+              +--------+               +--------+
           ^                      |                         |
           |     disable          |        complete         |
           +----------------------+-------------------------+
```

Every peripheral driver must implement explicit `enable()`, `disable()`, and `is_active()` methods. The power manager calls `disable()` when the peripheral reports idle.

