## Wake Source Management

### Wake Source Registry

| Wake Source | Event | Target Mode | Latency Budget |
|-------------|-------|-------------|----------------|
| RTC alarm | Periodic sampling | Stop -> Active | < 1 ms |
| GPIO (button) | User interaction | Standby -> Active | < 50 ms |
| UART RX | Incoming command | Stop -> Active | < 5 ms |
| Radio IRQ | Incoming packet | Stop -> Active | < 2 ms |
| Watchdog | Fault recovery | Any -> Reset | N/A |

### Wake Configuration Rules

- [ ] Only necessary wake sources are enabled for each sleep mode
- [ ] Wake source interrupt is configured before entering sleep
- [ ] Wake reason is logged after every wake (for power profiling)
- [ ] Spurious wake rate is measured (target: < 1 per hour)
- [ ] Wake latency measured on target hardware

