## Power Profiling

### Measurement Methods

| Method | Resolution | Use Case |
|--------|------------|----------|
| Multimeter (avg) | mA | Rough estimate |
| Current shunt + scope | uA, us resolution | Mode transition analysis |
| Nordic PPK / Joulescope | nA, us resolution | Full power profile |
| Coulomb counter IC | mAh | Long-term battery tracking |

### Profiling Checklist

- [ ] Each sleep mode current measured on target hardware
- [ ] Mode transition currents measured (spikes during wake)
- [ ] 24-hour power profile captured under realistic workload
- [ ] Battery life estimate validated against measured profile
- [ ] Power regression test: current draw compared across firmware versions

---

## Design Review Checklist

- [ ] Default GPIO state is lowest power (no floating inputs)
- [ ] Unused pins are tied to defined state (not floating)
- [ ] Pull-up/pull-down resistors accounted for in power budget
- [ ] External components (sensors, radios) have shutdown pins controlled by firmware
- [ ] Voltage regulators support low-Iq mode
- [ ] Debug interfaces (SWD, JTAG) can be disabled in production firmware
- [ ] Power-on sequence ensures no shoot-through or contention
